    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="l31XF5"&gt;Two years after announcing support, Ikea’s &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23420136/ikeas-dirigera-smart-home-review-price-specs"&gt;Dirigera hub&lt;/a&gt; can now be updated to act as a bridge between Ikea’s smart home devices and Matter-enabled systems. The software update builds upon &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/4/24087827/ikea-dirigera-hub-matter-support"&gt;early beta support&lt;/a&gt; by letting Ikea’s entire lineup of Zigbee-based smart home devices — like lights, blinds, controllers, air purifiers, and sensors — communicate with Matter-enabled devices from any company. &lt;/p&gt;
